cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.IR 

The paper deals with gait recognition using deep learning approaches, which is a computer vision problem (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of a generative adversarial network (GAN) for feature extraction, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of a large dataset, which could be considered as a multimedia dataset (cs.MM). Since the paper deals with surveillance and forensic applications, it could also be categorized under computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper involves the use of cross-view gait identification, which could be considered as an information retrieval problem (cs.IR).
